  "text": "One TFBS that did appear to be conserved between the species was the CCAAT box. This binds an evolutionarily conserved transcription factor that influences initiation and core motif recognition [CITATION_1] . On average, the CCAAT motif in Pl. halstedii resides slightly upstream of motifs such as INR + FPR (Fig. 6c) or the INR alone. Even though attempts to identify additional Pl. halstedii TFBSs using MEME with total promoters were unsuccessful, it may be possible to identify such motifs in future studies by evaluating the promoters of coregulated genes.",
